concept_explanation.recursion_stack:
**Recursion = implicit O(h) space (h = call depth):**

```java
// O(log n) space: binary search recursion
int binarySearch(int[] arr, int lo, int hi, int target) {
    if (lo > hi) return -1;
    int mid = lo + (hi - lo) / 2;
    return arr[mid] == target ? mid :
        arr[mid] < target ? binarySearch(arr, mid+1, hi, target)
                          : binarySearch(arr, lo, mid-1, target);
}
// Stack depth = log₂(n) frames → O(log n) space

// O(n) space: fibonacci recursion
int fib(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) return n;
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2); // up to n frames deep on left branch
}
// Stack depth = n frames → O(n) space
// (plus 2ⁿ time — worst of both worlds)

// Merge sort: O(n) space for temp arrays + O(log n) stack
// Total space: O(n)
```

